>Description:
When DrRacket opens, it says that teachpacks are loaded, but they aren't actually loaded until you press Run once.
>How-To-Repeat:
Open DrRacket and choose a teaching language. Select a teachpack, such as image. Hit Run. Quit DrRacket. Re-open DrRacket and you'll see that the teachpack is listed as loaded, however, if you type something like (circle 10 "solid" "blue"), it says "reference to an undefined identifier: circle". Clicking Run solves the problem.
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
