 On Sat, Sep 4, 2010 at 9:15 AM, Todd O'Bryan <toddobryan@gmail.com> wrote:
 > Yeah, I'd do (a).
 
 Thanks.
 
 > You could make students add teachpacks each time
 > they open DrScheme, I suppose, in which case (b) would become the de
 > facto behavior.
 
 I don't think that those two have to be connected. Option b) was meant
 to be "leave the contents of the repl alone, and make the printout
 match them".
 
 > But I don't think that makes sense with files that
 > have the teachpack listed.
 
 Are you referring to a 'require' in the program with this sentence? If
 so, perhaps it is worth noting that drracket does not show the
 "Teachpack:" line when you use require.
 
 Robby
 
