Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11160: loaded teachpacks must be Run before available
Date: Sat, 4 Sep 2010 10:18:21 -0500

 Oh, another point related to Shriram's comments. This is all about
 making the state and the GUI match. There are several pieces of state
 here: the teachacks that are selected and will be run next time you
 hit the "Run" button. The teachpacks that were loaded last time the
 "Run" button was clicked and then the initial state. Currently, the
 menu items reflect the first of those and the stuff following the word
 "Teachpack:" reflects the second, except (as Todd points out) in the
 initial, program-less REPL. So, one way to fix this is to just remove
 the line that begin with "Teachpack:" from the initial REPL. That was
 option b).
 
 Robby
 
 On Sat, Sep 4, 2010 at 10:15 AM, Robby Findler
