Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11160: loaded teachpacks must be Run before available
Date: Sat, 4 Sep 2010 11:25:18 -0400

 Can we agree on this?
 
 * It is a bug for DrRacket to print a Teachpack line but for those
 * Teachpacks to not actually be in the REPL.  Ever.  At start-up or at
 * any other time.
 
 Then, the two logical choices seem to be:
 
 1. DrRacket forgets about Teachpacks on exit.  On re-start, it neither
 prints a Teachpack line nor remembers.  Hitting F5 (w/ an empty
 buffer, etc.) will not cause any change to the REPL.
 
 2. DrRacket remembers Teachpacks on exit.  On re-start, the REPL
 prints the Teachpack line AND the Teachpack is available for use.
 
 I prefer #2.  A person using Teachpacks is likely a less sophisticated
 user (eg, middle-schooler in Bootstrap).  We shouldn't force them to
 constantly remember which Teachpacks they need; they get into a config
 for their course and would like to just leave it there.
 
 A user who switches between lots of configurations probably wouldn't
 be using the menu-based Teachpacks anyway, they'd just be using
 (require ...), and they would be unaffected by all this.
 
 [Curiously, I am myself an exception to this claim this semester.  But
 I still think #2 is the right thing for DrRacket to do.]
 
 Shriram
From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: Shriram Krishnamurthi <sk@cs.brown.edu>
Cc: Matthias Felleisen <matthias@ccs.neu.edu>,
        "Todd O'Bryan" <toddobryan@gmail.com>, bugs@racket-lang.org,
        nobody@racket-lang.org, bug-notification@racket-lang.org
