Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11160: loaded teachpacks must be Run before available
Date: Sat, 4 Sep 2010 13:19:18 -0400

 Matthias, dropping Teachpacks is not easy until creating languages is
 easy.
 
 Just this past month, I spent two weeks struggling to create a
 language for my course that was like ASL but had some added features.
 check-expect didn't work right, images in the REPL didn't work right,
 something else cropped up that my TAs had trouble explaining, and
 goodness knows what other mysteries lurked.  In desperation, the
 morning my class began, I finally tossed it all out and in 15 minutes
 created a Teachpack on top of ASL, and everything is just peachy.
 
 It may be I could have done the same with a language, but (a) the docs
 were just not up to it, (b) the replies I got on the list were only a
 approximation of what I needed, and (c) DrRacket isn't set up for
 this, either (since it hard-codes various languages) -- eg, if I were
 building on top of ISL, I still wouldn't get the Stepper.
 
 So no, it's not just Emu that's hurt.  DrRacket just isn't set up
 right now for languages to take the place of Teachpacks, and we need
 *something* to take their place for beginners of all shapes and sizes.
 
 Shriram
From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: Shriram Krishnamurthi <sk@cs.brown.edu>
Cc: Matthias Felleisen <matthias@ccs.neu.edu>,
        "Todd O'Bryan" <toddobryan@gmail.com>, bugs@racket-lang.org,
        nobody@racket-lang.org, bug-notification@racket-lang.org
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/11160: loaded teachpacks must be Run before available
