 On Sat, Sep 4, 2010 at 12:56 PM, Shriram Krishnamurthi <sk@cs.brown.edu> wr=
 ote:
 >> I'm sure you know most of this, Shriram, but the exercise of us
 >> getting "#lang htdp/isl" going is going to make this path smoother for
 >> those not familiar with the guts of Racket
 >
 > You're conflating Racket with DrRacket, which is (as far as I can
 > tell) incorrect. =C2=A0Even understanding Racket fairly well doesn't help
 > me know what on earth to do with DrRacket. =C2=A0Of course, lots of other
 > systems have the same problem (being proficient with Java doesn't make
 > you an expert in extending Eclipse).
 
 One way to look at this is that we're moving more and more to a place
 where drracket merely reflects what's in the definitions window with
 better ways to view it, etc. Thus all of the configuation / language
 building stuff becomes racket stuff, not drracket. (For example, the
 place where you got stuck with printing is all racket stuff, nothing
 to do with drracket).
 
 This definitely isn't true now, but that's where we're moving.
 
 I don't really think it is worth our time to spend too much energy
 emailing about this. The above is a short explanation and if you still
 don't agree, please just chalk it up to "you don't understand how
 things are organized in the guts" and come back in a few years and see
 if you change your mind.
 
 >> but (and this is where you may be
 >> disappointed) I don't think that the stepper is ever going to be
 >> language independent. At least not without research.
 >
 > You're responding to things I didn't even imply, much less say.
 
 The logic was supposed to go something like
 
 a) you said that you don't get various things, including the stepper
 
 b) I said that some of that will get better.
 
 c) I then meant to clarify that by saying "there are no plans for
 making the stepper better in this regard because we don't know how to"
 (hence enter research).
 
 Hope that clarifies.
 
 Robby
